<item>
            <title>[LU-1221] MMP failure info states &quot;Linux&quot; as the last update node</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-1221</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I&apos;ve noticed that when the MMP check fails that the message reported does not show the name of the host where the filesystem is mounted, the documents I&apos;ve seen on this imply that it it supposed to and the output makes it look like it is but the field says &quot;Linux&quot; instead of a hostname.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Example logs from both 2.1.1 and 1.8.6, both using the rpms provided by whamcloud.&lt;br/&gt;
2.1.1:&lt;br/&gt;
LDISKFS-fs warning (device dm-6): ldiskfs_multi_mount_protect: MMP failure info: last update time: 1331808934, last update node: Linux, last update device: dm-6&lt;br/&gt;
1.8.6:&lt;br/&gt;
LDISKFS-fs warning (device sfa0565): ldiskfs_multi_mount_protect: MMP failure info: last update time: 1331809026, last update node: Linux, last update device: sfa0472&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="13578">LU-1221</key>
